    "body": "<!--\r\n  Thank you for contributing to Neovim!\r\n  If this is your first time, check out https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests-prs\r\n  for our PR guidelines.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\nUI pickers for remote servers (like `:connect`) need to know which servers are actively used or stale. Currently, Nvim does not expose a mechanism to track user activity timestamps.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n- Introduce `v:lastactivity` as read-only Unix timestamp updated by `vgetc()` upon user keystrokes.\r\n- Throttle the update to 1-sec granularity to avoid overhead.\r\n- Expose this timestamp as `last_activity` in the dicts returned by `serverlist({info=true})` with internal RPC call.\r\n\r\n\r\nAddresses the `[last-activity]` requirement from #39420.\r\n\r\n**Note:** Stacked on top of #39392. Diff currently includes commits from the prerequisite PR, but will automatically shrink once #39392 merges into master.\r\n",
